4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, single-dose autoinjectible
6 epinephrine is the form of epinephrine approved to be
7 carried and self-administered by students, and
8 acquired, stocked, and administered by schools,
9 authorized entities, and certain staff members.
10 This bill would expand the type of approved
11 epinephrine to include any Food and Drug Administration
12 approved form of single-dose premeasured epinephrine
13 used to administer epinephrine into the human body to
14 prevent or treat a life-threatening allergic reaction.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Relating to public health; to amend Sections 16-1-39,
22 16-1-48, and 22-1-16, Code of Alabama 1975, to expand the form
23 of epinephrine approved to be carried and self-administered by
24 students, and stocked and administered by schools, authorized
25 entities, and certain staff members.
26 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
27 Section 1. Sections 16-1-39, 16-1-48, and 22-1-16, Code
28 of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
